# 📚 Learning Pandas: A Journey Through Reuven Lerner's "Pandas Workout"

Welcome to my repository where I document my journey of mastering the pandas library in Python. This project is inspired by the book _Pandas Workout: 200 Exercises to Make You a Stronger Data Analyst_ by Reuven Lerner. The book offers over 200 exercises designed to enhance your data analysis skills using pandas.

---

## 🧠 About the Book

In [_Pandas Workout_](http://www.manning.com/books/pandas-workout), Reuven Lerner guides readers through a series of exercises that cover essential tasks such as:

- Series and DataFrame operations
- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Grouping, merging, and reshaping data
- Time series analysis
- Data visualization
- Performance optimization

Each exercise is designed to be completed in about 10 minutes, providing hands-on experience with real-world data scenarios.

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

This repository mirrors the structure of the book, with each chapter represented as a folder containing:

- `exercise_X.ipynb`: Jupyter notebooks for each exercise I finished.
- `data/`: Sample datasets used in the exercises. Visit: [Reuven's reposetory](https://github.com/reuven/pandas-workout)
- `README.md`: This file, providing an overview and guidance.

---

